============================================================
PART 2 – MACHINE LEARNING
Football Match Prediction & Predictive Analytics
============================================================

Description:
After completing the SQL analytics and Python EDA stages,
the project moves from descriptive analytics into predictive
analytics using Machine Learning.

The previous sections transformed raw football match data
into structured analytical datasets containing:
- team performance metrics
- matchup statistics
- scoring behavior
- comparative strength indicators

These structured outputs created the foundation for applying
Machine Learning models capable of identifying statistical
patterns and generating football match predictions.

The ML phase focuses on head-to-head matches between the
Big 5 Premier League clubs:
- Arsenal
- Manchester City
- Manchester United
- Chelsea
- Liverpool

The objective is to predict:
1. Match outcomes (W1 / Draw / W2)
2. Over/Under 2.5 goals

This section demonstrates how structured football analytics
can evolve into a complete predictive modeling workflow.


============================================================
PROJECT STRUCTURE
============================================================

The Machine Learning workflow is organized into three main
Python scripts:

- ML_dataset.py
- ML_models.py
- ML_train.py

Together, these scripts create a complete pipeline for:
- dataset preparation
- feature engineering
- model training
- evaluation
- probability prediction
- final result generation


------------------------------------------------------------
1. ML_dataset.py
------------------------------------------------------------

ML_dataset.py is responsible for building the final
ML-ready dataset used for training.

The script combines:
- the original football match dataset
- SQL-generated team summaries
- SQL-generated matchup summaries

Using these datasets, the script performs feature
engineering by creating:
- team-level features
- comparative difference metrics
- matchup-based statistics

Examples include:
- team win rates
- average goal difference
- goals scored
- matchup intensity
- matchup dominance

The script also creates two prediction targets:
- match outcome prediction
- Over/Under 2.5 goals prediction

The final output is:

data/ml_ready/ml_1_big5_match_outcome_dataset.csv

This dataset becomes the foundation for all Machine Learning
experiments in the project.


------------------------------------------------------------
2. ML_models.py
------------------------------------------------------------

ML_models.py defines the Machine Learning models used for
prediction tasks.

Two classification models are implemented:

1. Logistic Regression
2. Random Forest Classifier

Logistic Regression is used for match outcome prediction
because it provides:
- interpretable results
- stable baseline performance
- probability estimation

Random Forest is used for Over/Under prediction because
it handles:
- non-linear relationships
- feature interactions
- complex football patterns

The models are implemented using Scikit-learn and organized
through reusable functions, creating a modular and scalable
training workflow.


------------------------------------------------------------
3. ML_train.py
------------------------------------------------------------

ML_train.py executes the complete training and evaluation
pipeline.

The script:
- loads the ML-ready dataset
- selects predictive features
- splits the data into training/testing sets
- trains the models
- evaluates performance
- exports predictions and probabilities

The evaluation process includes:
- accuracy score
- classification report
- confusion matrix
- prediction probabilities

The script also generates a final combined prediction table
containing:
- predicted match outcomes
- Over/Under predictions
- probability scores
- confidence values


============================================================
MACHINE LEARNING RESULTS
============================================================


------------------------------------------------------------
1. Match Outcome Prediction
(Logistic Regression)
------------------------------------------------------------

The Logistic Regression model was trained to predict:
- W1 → team_1 win
- D  → draw
- W2 → team_2 win

Final Accuracy:
- 40.74%

The model achieved its strongest performance when predicting
home wins (W1), while draw prediction remained the most
challenging due to the unpredictable nature of football
matches.

Despite the difficulty of multiclass sports prediction,
the model successfully identified meaningful statistical
patterns related to:
- team quality
- goal difference
- historical performance


------------------------------------------------------------
2. Over/Under 2.5 Goals Prediction
(Random Forest)
------------------------------------------------------------

The Random Forest model was trained to classify matches into:
- Over 2.5 goals
- Under 2.5 goals

Final Accuracy:
- 50.00%

The model achieved balanced performance across both classes,
demonstrating the ability to capture non-linear scoring
patterns and matchup relationships.

The results highlight the complexity of football scoring
behavior, where small tactical and statistical differences
can strongly influence goal production.


------------------------------------------------------------
Prediction Probability Analysis
------------------------------------------------------------

In addition to final predictions, the models generated
probability scores for every possible outcome.

This allowed the project to estimate:
- model confidence
- prediction uncertainty
- relative likelihood between outcomes

Instead of producing only a predicted label, the models also
provide probability-based football analysis, creating a more
realistic sports analytics workflow.


------------------------------------------------------------
Final Combined Predictions
------------------------------------------------------------

The final output of the pipeline is:

results/ml/final_combined_predictions.csv

This file combines:
- match outcome probabilities
- Over/Under probabilities
- predicted labels
- confidence scores

The final CSV provides a compact and interpretable summary
of the Machine Learning predictions and represents the final
predictive output of the complete football analytics project.


